{
  "texts": [
    "These techniques can be categorized into four groups, primarily distinguished by the choice of parameters to train [33].",
    "This often results in a trade-off among memory footprint, computational overhead, and performance.",
    "A summary is depicted in Figure 1.The most straightforward way to avoid full fine-tuning is through selective methods, which focus on a subset of the existing model weights.",
    "Among these, BitFit [56] fine-tunes only the biases of both the attention and MLP layers in the transformer blocks, while other approaches prune the model to create a task-specific subset of parameters [15,19].Secondly, adapters integrate additional trainable modules into the original frozen architecture [6,20,25,34,44]; for example, by shifting and scaling deep features [34].",
    "They also demonstrate their versatility and effectiveness in various tasks implying vision and language [47]."
  ]
}